snippet.textDisplay: *suicide. It was suicide so the cops wouldn’t search his jet and he would go to jail. No hate on Jarad, but it was kind of a dumb move on his part. He shoved a bunch of pain killers down his throat once he found out there were cops waiting for him at the airport. (When I mean a he shoved a whole shot bunch in his mouth, obviously a dangerous move) I don’t know what he thought the outcome would be, maybe he knew his body would react that way, but not so bad that it would of killed him, but it did. Anyway, just saying that from the news articles, the way they’re projecting it the situation/ cause of Jarad’s death to be is not true. He did not just suddenly drop and have a seizure for no damn reason. His brain rejected his body (or vice versa) when he “overdosed” on the opioids. After the fact, they did/ are searching the private jet in which Jarad was flying on.  Considering the facts, many would say that he committed suicide to stop the outcome of his horrible decision and be sent to jail on a count of the almost 4+ charges to his name. Condolences to his family and girlfriend, again, I don’t hate him, just literally saying the truth.
